definition: to close/to stop up/to shut/to obstruct
aspect particle indicating action in progress
to make known/to show/to prove/to write/book/outstanding
to touch/to come in contact with/to feel/to be affected by/to catch fire/to burn/(coll.) to fall asleep/(after a verb) hitting the mark/succeeding in

sentences.english: It lay there with its eyes closed, dead as a doornail.
sentences.chinese: 它躺在那裏眼睛閉著，確實死了。

sentences.english: Why are you looking at the mirror with your eyes shut?
sentences.chinese: 你爲什麼閉著眼睛照鏡子呢？

sentences.english: At this point you may be able to see through your closed eyes.
sentences.chinese: 此時也許你閉著眼睛，卻看得見東西。
